  m_text: "- B\xFAn D\u1EADu M\u1EAFm T\xF4m is a traditional Northern Vietnamese
    meal featuring rice noodles, fried tofu, herbs, and fermented shrimp paste.\n\n-
    It is often eaten as a casual street food meal shared among family and friends.\n\n-
    The dish is known for its simple ingredients and strong cultural identity in
    Hanoi.\n\n- Common additions include pork, fried spring rolls, and cucumber."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f6b83f304dc3a98448bbbbe575dcc972, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -7784278538909227094, guid: f6b83f304dc3a98448bbbbe575dcc972, type: 2}
